05426nam a22009255i 9783035624205DE-B159720220110023848.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||220110t20212022sz     fo  d z      eng d  a2021934004  a97830356242057 a10.1515/97830356242052doi  a(DE-B1597)579283  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  aszcCH 7aDES0000002bisacsh1 aWohlgemuth, Caroline, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aMid-Century Modern – Visionary Furniture Design from Vienna /cCaroline Wohlgemuth. 1aBasel : bBirkhäuser, c[2021] 4c©2022  a1 online resource (296 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aEdition Angewandte ,x1866-248X0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aIn 1938, Vienna lost its best and most creative minds. This rupture was manifested in all of the arts and sciences and its mark is felt to this day – not least in the field of furniture design. With inexhaustible creativity the Jewish furniture designers who were forced to flee Vienna continued to work while in exile. They taught at the best universities and spread their ideas and vision throughout the entire world. Their creations became classics of twentieth-century furniture design, the epitome of mid-century modern style. This book honors the memory of the exiled designers with a thorough overview of their work. It details their life stories and their visionary designs, which remain as relevant and contemporary as ever, and brings to light new aspects of the history of Viennese furniture design.  aWien verlor im Jahr 1938 seine kreativsten und besten Köpfe: Ein Riss in der Zeit, der sich quer durch alle Wissenschaften und Künste manifestierte und bis heute spürbar bleibt – auch im Möbeldesign. Mit ihrer unerschöpflichen Kreativität wirkten die vertriebenen jüdischen Möbeldesignerinnen und -designer aus Wien im Exil weiter. Sie unterrichteten an den besten Universitäten und verbreiteten ihre Ideen und Visionen auf der gesamten Welt. Ihre Möbel wurden zu Designklassikern des 20. Jahrhunderts, zum Inbegriff des Mid-Century Modern Style. Dieser Überblick ruft das Möbeldesign der vertriebenen Designerinnen und Designer in Erinnerung: Er vergegenwärtigt ihre Lebensgeschichten und ihre visionären Entwürfe, die heute aktueller sind denn je, und fördert neue Aspekte der Geschichte des Möbeldesigns aus Wien zutage.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 10. Jan 2022) 4aDesign. 4aInnenarchitektur. 4aMid-Century Modern. 4aMöbel. 7aDESIGN / General.2bisacsh  aDesign.  aMid-Century Modern.  afurniture.  ainterior design.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2021z978311075072008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2021 Part 1z978311075070608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2022 Part 1z978311076682008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Architecture and Design 2021z9783110753783oZDB-23-DAD08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2021 Englishz978311075403208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton Architecture eBooks 2021z97831107565930 cprintz978303562409040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978303562420540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783035624205423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783035624205/original  a978-3-11-075070-6  DG Plus DeG Package 2021 Part 1b2021  a978-3-11-075072-0  DG Ebook Package English 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  